&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Biomedical Scientist/ Trainee Biomedical Scientist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agenda for Change Band 5 (Annex 21 for trainee): £24 907 - £30 615&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agenda for Change Band 6: £31 365 - £37 890&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 Contract: Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an opportunity for an HCPC Registered Biomedical Scientist join our team in the Immunology laboratory service at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals. Training will be provided in all sections of the laboratory. This post could be appointable at either trainee, BMS5 or BMS6 level dependent on experience and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered Biomedical Scientists will be encouraged to undertake the IBMS Specialist Portfolio in Immunology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Immunology and Protein Reference Unit is situated on the Northern General Hospital campus in new purpose built laboratories. The department has an extensive repertoire of immunology and specialist protein tests with samples referred from all over the UK and further afield. There is also a proactive programme of new assay development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous relevant laboratory experience would be considered essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information contact either Jonathan Aldis – Laboratory Manager on 0114 271 5719 or Andy Richardson – Chief BMS on 0114 271 5718.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
